RedMere Technology allows these cables to support the full 18Gbps to longer distances while using thinner conductors than ordinary cables. A typical passive High Speed HDMI Cable can reach a maximum length of 25 feet using 22AWG conductors which results in a cable as thick as your index finger. On the other hand High Speed HDMI Cables with RedMere Technology can deliver the full 18Gbps bandwidth to up to 60 feet using 28AWG conductors which results in a cable about half the diameter.

While existing High Speed HDMI Cables can handle each individual feature in the new spec real-world video usage usually employs more than one HDMI feature at the same time. The difference between the older 10.2Gbps cables and these newer 18Gbps cables is the need to compromise in your choices versus no need for compromise.

In addition to all the High Speed HDMI features these cables support all of the following features from the latest HDMI spec:

* Up to 32 audio channels

* Dynamic synchronization of audio and video streams

{u'Product Short Description': [u'StarTech.com 2 Port USB DVI KVM Switch with DDM Fast Switching Technology and Cables - 2 Computer(s) - 1 Local User(s) - 1920 x 1200 - 1 x Network (RJ-45) - 6 x USB - 3 x DVI'], u'Category': [u'KVM Switch'], u'Product Segment': [u'Electronics'], u'Assembled Product Length': [u'6.5'], u'Manufacturer Part Number': [u'SV231DVIUDDM'], u'Country of Origin: Components': [u'USA and/or Imported'], u'UPC': [u'67OMaI5F2825'], u'GTIN': [u'II67OMaI5F2825'], u'Assembled Product Width': [u'3.0'], u'Product Name': [u'StarTech.com 2 Port USB DVI KVM Switch with DDM Fast Switching Technology and Cables - 2 Computer(s) - 1 Local User(s) -'], u'Assembled Product Height': [u'1.7'], u'Product Type': [u'KVM Switches'], u'Warranty Information': [u'Y'], u'Condition': [u'New'], u'Product Long Description': [u'

The SV231DVIUDDM 2-Port USB DVI KVM Switch lets you control 2 DVI, USB-equipped PCs using a single peripheral set at high-definition DVI resolutions up to 1920x1200.

The included KVM cables provide a ready-out-of-the-box solution, while USB Dynamic Device Mapping (DDM) and Display Data Channel (DDC) features work to significantly reduce switching lag-time and improve overall compatibility with your connected display and input devices, saving you time and money.

For the next level in KVM performance, this DVI KVM switch integrates dual-core dedicated processing per channel and innovative, USB DDM technology that enables you to quickly switch between connected computers with next-to-zero delay. DDM maintains a constant communication channel between your USB peripherals and connected systems, avoiding the time necessary for your systems to re-recognize the devices when switching.

In addition to faster switching, the KVM offers All-time Display Data Channel (Full DDC) technology to maintain proper display detection among connected systems, a simple one-touch button for hot-key selection and an integrated 2-port USB hub allowing you to share additional peripherals.

{u'Product Short Description': [u'Speed up your wired internet connection using this USB 3.0 Gigabit Ethernet Adapter from Monoprice!

This adapter allows you to get improved network speeds on any laptop or on a desktop without having to install a new network card. It features 1000 Mbps Gigabit Ethernet speeds and is backwards compatible with 10/100 Mbps connections. The SuperSpeed USB 3.0 interface means that the USB port will not slow down your Gigabit Ethernet speed.

The adapter draws all the power it needs from the USB port it is plugged into and therefore needs no external power supply or source.
